stice","2017-11-14","Mentally Disordered Offenders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how much funding has been allocated to the Mental Health Casework Section in each year since 2009-10; and how many full-time equivalent staff have been employed by that section in each of those years.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","112879"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789154","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-11-20","<p>A variety of products have been available for some time to assist different types of litigant with the costs of claims, including court fees, such as after the event insurance.</p><p>Third party litigation funding is typically used as a form of funding in very high value commercial litigation.</p><p>Support for paying court fees is available for people bringing courts and tribunals proceedings through the Help with Fees scheme, subject to meeting the capital and income tests. Under this scheme, those who qualify may have their court fees remitted in part or in full.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2017-11-20T17:37:44.853Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789154/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789154/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789154/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-11-14","Civil Proceedings: Legal Costs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what assessment he has made of the implications for his policies of litigants having to turn to third-party funders to meet the cost of issuing proceedings.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","112801"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789155","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-11-21","<p>There are no plans to implement a policy of this nature.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-11-21T15:58:40.283Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789155/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789155/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789155/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-11-14","Ministry of Justice: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 10 November 2017, to Question 111090, if he will make it his policy to collate data on incoming telephone calls and charges to devolved organisations who work under contract to his Department.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","112951"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789156","Home Office","false","2017-11-17","<p>The Home Office does not hold the data requested in a reportable format.</p><p>Every individual detained under Immigration Act powers is eligible to apply for release on bail. Such bail applications may be made to the Home Office and/or to an independent judge of the First-tier Tribunal. Detained individuals may apply for bail at any time.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-11-17T09:18:44.64Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789156/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789156/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789156/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-11-14","Bail: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many bail applications were made by EU nationals held in immigration detention in the last 12 months; and how many of those applications were successful.","false","Biography information for Anneliese Dodds","Oxford East","Anneliese Dodds","112923"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789157","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-11-21","<p>The Government set out its ambition for a reformed prison estate in the November 2016 Prison Safety and Reform White Paper. Our reforms will close down ageing and ineffective prisons and replace them with buildings fit for today’s demands. The new prison estate will create the physical conditions for Governors to achieve better educational, training and rehabilitation outcomes.</p><p> </p><p>No decision has yet been made on who will operate the new prisons.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-11-21T15:41:18.823Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789157/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789157/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789157/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-11-14","Prisons: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether his Department plans to build new private prisons.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","113011"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789158","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-11-20","<p>On behalf of the Government I have been engaging intensively with the parties and, as appropriate, the Irish Government towards the restoration of devolution in Northern Ireland. The parties have made significant progress but some issues remain outstanding. Our focus now needs to be on finding a compromise on these issues. At present, I believe the parties are best placed to do this through direct discussion, with the support of the UK Government and the Irish Government in accordance with the three stranded approach.</p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2017-11-20T11:49:12.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789158/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789158/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789158/answer",,,,,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-11-14","Northern Ireland Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, if he will appoint an independent person to chair the talks between the main political parties in Northern Ireland to agree the means for restoring a functioning assembly at Stormont; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","112874"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789159","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-11-20","<p>The remit of the advice sought from Mr Trevor Reaney does include support and provision for the employment of Members’ staff. The full remit is set out in my letter to Mr Reaney and is available on the Northern Ireland Office website:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/659476/mla_pay_letter__scanned_.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/659476/mla_pay_letter__scanned_.pdf</a></p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2017-11-20T11:51:32.66Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789159/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789159/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789159/answer",,,,,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-11-14","Northern Ireland Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, pursuant to his oral contribution of 13 November 2017, Official Report, column 72, for what reasons the full staffing allowances of MLAs have been omitted from the remit of the independent review announced on 13 November 2017; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","112883"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789160","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-11-20","<p>I can confirm that I intend to publish Mr Reaney’s advice as to how we should approach pay and allowances for Members of the Northern Ireland Assembly in the continued absence of an Executive.</p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2017-11-20T11:55:12.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789160/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789160/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789160/answer",,,,,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-11-14","Northern Ireland Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, pursuant to his oral contribution of 13 November 2017, Official Report, column 72, if he will confirm that the independent assessment being undertaken into the continued payment of MLA salaries in the absence of a functioning Assembly will be published; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","112884"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789161","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-11-20","<p>As made clear in our Position Paper on Northern Ireland and Ireland, published in August, and in the Prime Minister’s Florence speech in September, we remain firmly committed to avoiding a hard border, including no physical infrastructure between Northern Ireland and Ireland. This is a point on which we have remained clear throughout.</p><p>In doing so, there can be no border between Great Britain and Northern Ireland or anything that fractures the internal market of the United Kingdom, which benefits Northern Ireland hugely.</p><p> </p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith",,"2017-11-20T11:53:12.733Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789161/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789161/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789161/answer",,,,,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-11-14","Borders: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what progress has been made on defining the nature of the border between the UK and the Republic of Ireland after the UK leaves the EU; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Peter Bone","Wellingborough","Mr Peter Bone","112990"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789162","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-11-21","<p>In September 2014, the Government set out its position in relation to the ‘on the runs’ administrative scheme fully in a statement to the House of Commons. In the statement, the Government was clear that the scheme was at an end and that there was no basis for any reliance on letters received by so-called “On The Runs” under the scheme that was introduced by the previous Labour Government.</p><p> </p><p>I have said on a number of occasions there is no amnesty, immunity or exemption from prosecution. This was confirmed by Lady Justice Hallett in her review of the scheme published in July 2014. This Government’s position is very clear. Those who received letters under the scheme should be in no doubt: if there is considered to be sufficient evidence of their involvement in any crime, they will be investigated by the police and prosecuting authorities.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>This Government’s position with regards to publishing the names of individuals in receipt of letters under the OTR scheme is unchanged. We do not consider it appropriate to publish the names for a number of reasons including because it could jeopardise future prosecutions or increase the risk of an abuse of process argument being successfully run.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2017-11-21T11:00:51.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789162/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789162/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789162/answer",,,,,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-11-14","Charles Caulfield","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, whether Charlie Caulfield received a letter of comfort.","false","Biography information for Kate Hoey","Vauxhall","Kate Hoey","112966"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789163","Prime Minister","false","2017-11-22","<p>The Expert Working Group of the Commission on Human Medicines on hormone pregnancy tests is independent of Government. It published its report on Wednesday 15 November. The Department of Health is now focused on implementing the review’s recommendations to safeguard future generations by further strengthening the systems in place for detecting, evaluating and communicating safety concerns with use of medicines in pregnancy.</p>","Maidenhead","Mrs Theresa May",,"2017-11-22T15:37:57.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789163/answer","Biography information for Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789163/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789163/answer",,,,,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2017-11-14","Pregnancy Tests","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, what meetings she has had with (a) hon. Members and (b) external experts on (i) hormone pregnancy tests and (ii) the Expert Working Group on hormone pregnancy tests.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","112844"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789164","Department for Transport","false","2017-11-22","<p>The Government is considering carefully all the potential implications arising from the UK’s exit from the EU, including the implications for continued or discontinued participation in the European Aviation Safety Agency.</p><p> </p><p>The nature of the UK’s future participation with the Agency will be a matter for the negotiations.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-11-22T12:28:21.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789164/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789164/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789164/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-11-14","European Aviation Safety Agency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether the UK plans to participate in the European Aviation Safety Agency after the UK has left the EU.","false","Biography information for Stephen Kinnock","Aberavon","Stephen Kinnock","112898"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789165","Department for Transport","false","2017-11-20","<p>In his Written Ministerial Statement of 20 July 2017, the Transport Secretary made clear that he is committed to developing options to improve journeys for rail passengers across Wales including station improvements at Cardiff Station.</p><p> </p><p>The Cardiff Station to which the Transport Secretary was referring to in his statement was Cardiff Central Station.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-11-20T15:43:50.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789165/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789165/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789165/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-11-14","Railway Stations: Cardiff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to his Written Ministerial Statement of 20 July 2017, HCWS85, on rail update, which Cardiff station is the intended recipient of funds for improvements referred to.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","112875"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789166","Department for Transport","false","2017-11-20","<p>As the independent regulator, the ORR has consumer law powers to protect passengers’ rights. The Government, in its guidance to ORR this July, made clear that the ORR should use these powers to hold industry to account.</p><p> </p><p>In June, ORR published the results of its audit of train operator websites against the Retail Code of Practice, and has identified areas for improvement in its consumer report. An update of this will be published in December.</p><p> </p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-11-20T15:19:43.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789166/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789166/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789166/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-11-14","Railways: Tickets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent assessment he has made of the effectiveness of Office of Rail and Road's enforcement of train-operating company licence provisions in terms of their meeting their retail code of practice obligations; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","112876"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789167","Department for Transport","false","2017-11-20","<p>The Department for Transport does not hold information on the Rail Delivery Group’s spending on marketing and advertising.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-11-20T15:07:25.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789167/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789167/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789167/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-11-14","Rail Delivery Group: Marketing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how much the Rail Delivery Group spent on marketing and advertising in (a) 2016-17, (b) 2015-16 and (c) 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","112937"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789168","Department for Transport","false","2017-11-20","<p>The Government is supportive of the Rail Delivery Group’s role of providing industry leadership in the railway to achieve better outcomes for rail users. We continue to work closely with them to ensure they are well placed to provide the strategic leadership needed to deliver key reforms in the railway.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-11-20T15:10:51.08Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789168/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789168/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789168/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-11-14","Rail Delivery Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of the Rail Delivery Group; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","112938"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789169","Department for Transport","false","2017-11-22","<p>The safety of those who travel on offshore helicopter flights is paramount. In 2013 the Civil Aviation Authority (CAA) launched a comprehensive review of offshore helicopter flying, resulting in a step change in safety that was welcomed by everyone involved. The review is available at <a href="http://www.caa.co.uk/cap1145" target="_blank">www.caa.co.uk/cap1145</a>.</p><p> </p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-11-22T12:20:14.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789169/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789169/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789169/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-11-14","Offshore Industry: Helicopters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent assessment his Department has made of trends in the safety of helicopter transport in the offshore oil and gas sector.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","112798"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789170","Department for Transport","false","2017-11-22","<p>The Civil Aviation Authority monitors the ability of UK operators to obtain such insurance. The ability of UK licence holders to obtain insurance cover is dependent upon the insurer’s assessment of relevant risks in relation to an individual licence holder. The CAA advises that such cover in the market in general has been readily obtainable over the period in question, and the overall market trend of such premiums has been downwards.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-11-22T12:17:19.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789170/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789170/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789170/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-11-14","Offshore Industry: Helicopters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent information his Department holds on trends in the cost of insuring commercial helicopter flights in the North Sea oil and gas industry since January 2009 to date.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","112799"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789171","Department for Transport","false","2017-11-16","<p>The body of water defined as The Solent is neither classified as an estuary nor as open-water. The Solent is a strait that separates the Isle of Wight from mainland England. For the purposes of safe navigation and equipment requirements for ships, the Solent is classified as Category D waters, defined as ‘tidal rivers and estuaries where the significant wave height could not be expected to exceed 2.0 metres at any time’.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-11-16T14:11:03.06Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789171/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789171/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789171/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-11-14","Solent","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether the Government classifies the Solent as (a) an estuary or (b) open water.","false","Biography information for Mr Bob Seely","Isle of Wight","Mr Bob Seely","112816"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789172","Department for Transport","false","2017-11-22","<p>The Government is considering carefully all the potential implications arising from the UK’s exit from the EU, including the implications for the continued participation in the European Union Agency for Railways.</p><p> </p><p>The UK’s continued participation with the Agency as a third country, as well as continued cooperation in the field of rail safety and standards, will be a matter for negotiations.</p><p> </p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-11-22T13:31:04.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789172/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789172/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789172/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-11-14","European Union Agency for Railways","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to Article 75 of EU Regulation 2016/796, whether the UK plans to seek formal third country participation with the European Union Agency for Railways after the UK has left the EU.","false","Biography information for Stephen Kinnock","Aberavon","Stephen Kinnock","113027"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789173","Department for Transport","false","2017-11-22","<p>The department does not have any plans to reinstate the train station in Consett.</p><p> </p><p>In line with our devolution policies, it is for the Local Enterprise Partnerships (LEPs) and local transport authorities in this area to decide what are the priority projects to support economic development and to secure appropriate funding - including drawing on that made available by Government for example through the Local Growth Fund - to take them forward.</p><p> </p><p>Proposals for new stations need first to secure the support of a local promoter, normally the local transport authority, to undertake studies of the potential additional passenger demand, train service options, economic benefits, capital and any operating subsidy requirements before the addition of such services to a franchise agreement could be considered.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-11-22T13:35:11.19Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789173/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789173/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789173/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-11-14","Consett Station","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether his Department has made an assessment of the feasibility of reinstating the train station in Consett; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Laura Pidcock","North West Durham","Laura Pidcock","113009"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789174","Department for Transport","false","2017-11-20","<p>The Rail Delivery Group (RDG) is a private company funded by the membership fees paid by its members, which comprise Network Rail (a public body) and train company owning groups (which are private companies). The Department for Transport does not hold information as regards any specific contribution to In Partnership for Britain’s Prosperity made by Network Rail. The Department was not required to approve any funding.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-11-20T15:13:45.113Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789174/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789174/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789174/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-11-14","Rail Delivery Group: Marketing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the cost to the public purse has been of (a) marketing and (b) advertising associated with the Rail Delivery Group's In Partnership for Britain's Prosperity campaign.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","112935"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789175","Department for Transport","false","2017-11-20","<p>The Rail Ombudsman is being introduced on a voluntary basis. In this way, the scheme will be delivered far more quickly than could be achieved through a compulsory route, enabling the benefits to be felt by passengers as soon as possible. The Rail Delivery Group issued a press release on 4 August 2017 confirming that the train companies have collectively committed to introducing a new independent ombudsman to investigate and rule on unresolved customer complaints.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-11-20T15:16:30.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789175/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789175/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789175/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-11-14","Railways: Ombudsman","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether train-operating company participation in the Rail Ombudsman will be compulsory.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","112936"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789176","Department for Transport","false","2017-11-21","<p>Road investment in Scotland is a devolved matter and as such any plans to regenerate the A75 euro-route fall to the Scottish Government.</p><p> </p><p>Where there are areas of cross border interest, such as in the case of the A1 north of Newcastle, UK ministers are keen to collaborate with their Scottish counterparts.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-11-21T12:47:27.903Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789176/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789176/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789176/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-11-14","A75: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what discussions he has had with his counterpart in the Scottish Government about regeneration of the A75 euro-route from Gretna to Stranraer.","false","Biography information for Mr Alister Jack","Dumfries and Galloway","Mr Alister Jack","112894"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789177","Department for Transport","false","2017-11-22","<p>The Government is considering carefully all the potential implications arising from the UK’s exit from the EU.</p><p> </p><p>The Government plans to negotiate the best possible relationship between the UK and the EU in the field of aviation, and will have the resources and staff to do so.</p><p> </p><p>We are approaching the discussions with ambition, seeking to give citizens and businesses as much certainty as possible, as early as possible. It will be in the interests of all sides in this negotiation to maintain closely integrated aviation markets, as other EU Member States recognise.</p><p> </p><p>We will continue to work closely with the international aviation community to ensure that this global industry continues to be a major success story for the UK economy.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-11-22T12:25:14.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789177/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789177/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789177/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-11-14","Air Transport Agreements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he is taking to ensure agreements are in place between each EU member state and the UK to enable the provisions of the European Common Aviation Area to continue to apply after the UK leaves the EU; when he plans to put those agreements in place; and whether his Department plans to take on additional staff or other resources to meet that timetable.","false","Biography information for Sir Vince Cable","Twickenham","Sir Vince Cable","112942"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789178","Department for Transport","false","2017-11-21","<p>Road investment in Scotland is a devolved power and as such any plans to upgrade the A75 fall to the Scottish Government.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-11-21T12:44:49.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789178/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789178/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789178/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-11-14","A75: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans he has to upgrade the A75 euro-route from Gretna to Stranraer.","false","Biography information for Mr Alister Jack","Dumfries and Galloway","Mr Alister Jack","112893"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789179","Wales Office","false","2017-11-20","<p>I hold regular discussions with Cabinet colleagues, including the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, on a range of issues, including the impact of EU exit on Wales.</p><p> </p><p>The Department for Exiting the European Union, working with officials across Government, including the Office of the Secretary of State for Wales, is undertaking a wide range of analysis covering the entirety of the UK economy, including Wales, to support the negotiations.</p><p> </p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2017-11-20T12:56:35.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789179/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789179/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789179/answer",,,,,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2017-11-14","Economic Situation: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, if he will have discussions with the Department for Exiting the European Union on conducting an assessment of the potential outcomes of the UK's negotiations with the EU on the Welsh economy.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","112984"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789180","Wales Office","false","2017-11-20","<p>The Government is committed to the best possible deal for the United Kingdom; a deal that works for Scotland, Wales, Northern Ireland and all parts of England.</p><p> </p><p>It is not standard practice to provide an ongoing commentary on internal analytical work that is being carried out within government. We have also been very clear that we must not publish material that could undermine the UK position in the negotiations.</p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2017-11-20T12:58:56.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789180/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789180/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789180/answer",,,,,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2017-11-14","Economic Situation: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, pursuant to the Answer of 7 November 2017 to Question 111256, on economic situation: Wales, what the outcome of the economic analysis has been to date.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","112873"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789181","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-11-21","<p>The costs referred to in the response to the Answer of 3 November 2017 to Question 110379 on Tidal Lagoons was a contract between the Hendry Review and ITPE Ltd (now known as ITPEnergised) for the provision of expert consultancy advice to support the work of the Review. The value of the contract was £117,729.60</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-11-21T14:28:33.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789181/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789181/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789181/answer",,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-11-14","Tidal Lagoons Independent Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, pursuant to the Answer of 3 November 2017 to Question 110379, on Tidal Lagoons Independent Review, if he will (a) set out the costs that make up that approximate figure and (b) place the evidential basis for those costs in the Library.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","112869"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789182","Women and Equalities","false","2017-11-22","<p>The Government Equalities Office does not monitor the relative incidence of discrimination against people with different disabilities and health conditions.</p><p> </p><p>The Equality Act 2010 provides protection from disability discrimination to all those who meet its definition of disability: ‘a physical or mental impairment which has a substantial and long-term adverse effect on a person’s ability to carry out normal day-to-day activities’.</p><p> </p><p>It does not, except in a few specific instances, list conditions that fall within this definition. Instead in most cases, the impact on the person’s life is the qualifying criteria for determining a disability rather than the condition itself.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-11-22T16:44:22.053Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789182/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789182/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789182/answer",,,,,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2017-11-14","Diabetes: Discrimination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, what assessment she has made of the extent of disability discrimination against those with (a) type 1 and (b) type 2 diabetes; and what steps are being taken to address disability discrimination for people with diabetes.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","112908"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789183","Women and Equalities","false","2017-11-22","<p>The Government wishes to have a constructive relationship with the EU following the UK’s exit. This also applies to our relationship with the EU's agencies and bodies.</p><p> </p><p>No decisions have yet been made on the our future relationship with the European Institute for Gender Equality after leaving the EU.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2017-11-22T16:01:25.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789183/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789183/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789183/answer",,,,,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2017-11-14","European Institute for Gender Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, with reference to Article 8 of EU Regulation No 1922/2006, whether the UK plans to seek formal cooperation with the European Institute for Gender Equality after the UK has left the EU.","false","Biography information for Stephen Kinnock","Aberavon","Stephen Kinnock","113029"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789184","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-11-20","<p>I refer the Member to the answer given on 8 November 17 to question <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=50&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;dept=29&amp;uin=110869" target="_blank">110869</a></p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-11-20T18:03:41.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789184/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789184/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789184/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-11-14","Universal Credit: Warrington North","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many and what proportion of universal credit claimants in Warrington North constituency have an advance payment agreement.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","113021"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789185","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-11-20","<p>There are an estimated <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/603004/outturn-and-forecast-spring-budget-2017.ods" target="_blank">124,000 SMI claimants</a>. We are not able to provide estimates of SMI claimants at a constituency level.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-11-20T12:26:12.103Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789185/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789185/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789185/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-11-14","Support for Mortgage Interest: North West Durham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what proportion of people in North West Durham Constituency will be affected by the Support for Mortgage Interest benefit becoming a loan.","false","Biography information for Laura Pidcock","North West Durham","Laura Pidcock","113010"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789186","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-11-20","<p>Jobcentre Plus does not make direct referrals to food banks but has offered a signposting service since 2011 to those who have expressed an interest in using a foodbank. No data is held on the number using the signposting service in the Halton and Cheshire West and Chester local authority area.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-11-20T16:43:53.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789186/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789186/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789186/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-11-14","Food Banks: Cheshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate his Department has made of the number of people referred to foodbanks by Jobcentre Plus in the Halton and Cheshire West and Chester local authority areas in each of the last seven years.","false","Biography information for Mike Amesbury","Weaver Vale","Mike Amesbury","113017"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789187","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-11-20","<p>It is not the Government’s role to determine whether the individual underlying investments of pension schemes are safe or not. The Government has, however, legislated to require trustees or managers of occupational pension schemes to ensure the quality and security of their scheme’s investment portfolio. This includes ensuring that scheme assets are predominantly invested in investments admitted to regulated markets.</p><p> </p><p>Pension providers of workplace personal pensions need to be authorised by the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA) in order to carry out this activity. The FCA is also responsible for the regulation of the investment market and financial advisers. FCA already holds a register of firms that are or have been regulated by them or the Prudential Regulation Authority. The register is open to the public. FCA also produces a warning list that the public, including trustees, can use to check an investment or pension opportunity to avoid scams.</p>","Hexham","Guy Opperman",,"2017-11-20T12:05:42.713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789187/answer","Biography information for Guy Opperman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789187/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789187/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-11-14","Pensions: Regulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 11 October 2017 to Question 106439, on pensions, other than Master Trusts, if the Government will establish an approved list of regulated pension schemes with regulated underlying investments that are deemed safe; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","112927"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789188","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-11-20","<p>This consultation, which closed on 1 October 2017, sought views on the approach to address the bridging pensions anomaly within Pension Protection Fund compensation. The vast majority of consultation respondents agreed that the anomaly should be addressed. However, a significant number were in favour of an alternative approach which more closely reflected the original pension scheme rules and after careful consideration, the Government has decided to proceed with this alternative. On Friday 17 November 2017, my Department launched a technical consultation on the draft regulations to implement this scheme rules based approach.</p>","Hexham","Guy Opperman",,"2017-11-20T12:19:49.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789188/answer","Biography information for Guy Opperman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789188/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789188/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-11-14","Pensions: Regulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, when he will respond to the consultation, Pension Protection Fund: draft regulations to take account of bridging pensions, published on 31 August 2017.","false","Biography information for Jessica Morden","Newport East","Jessica Morden","112928"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789189","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-11-20","<p>The Autism Act 2009 does not impose any specific statutory obligations on DWP or its Providers. The Department is, however, fully committed to improving the services it provides for people with autism. Part of the Department’s Autism Strategy Action Plan focuses on key areas for improvement, including promotion of the autism agenda to our Assessment Provider, Centre for Health and Disability Assessments. In order to improve the skills and knowledge of Healthcare Professionals that undertake Work Capability Assessments, the Department supported the Centre for Health and Disability Assessments in the development of condition specific training on autism which is quality assured by external reviewers.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-11-20T15:50:57.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789189/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789189/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789189/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-11-14","Work Capability Assessment: Autism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps his Department has taken to ensure that training offered to those carrying out work capability assessments complies with statutory obligations under the Autism Act 2009.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","112979"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789190","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-11-20","<p>Since May-July 2016, the employment rate has increased by 0.6 percentage points to reach 75.0 per cent in July-September 2016. The unemployment rate has decreased by 0.7 percentage points to 4.3 per cent over the same period, the lowest rate since 1975.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-11-20T12:13:33.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789190/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789190/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789190/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-11-14","Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the change in the rate of (a) employment and (b) unemployment since 23 June 2016.","false","Biography information for Mr Peter Bone","Wellingborough","Mr Peter Bone","112991"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789191","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-11-20","<p>Work Coaches work closely with jobseekers to help them move towards employment and can offer a wide range of support tailored to the specific needs of customers, including those with health conditions and disabilities.</p><p> </p><p>There is a wide range of local and national contracted and non-contracted provision and support available to customers, and their Work Coach will refer them to the most appropriate support available locally.</p><p> </p><p>In areas where the Work and Health Programme has not yet rolled out, contracts for other provision have been extended to ensure we can continue to meet the on-going needs of customers.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-11-20T16:40:53.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789191/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789191/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789191/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-11-14","Unemployment: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what support job coaches are able to offer jobseekers with health conditions and disabilities in the event that those jobcentres are unable to access the Work and Health programme.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","113000"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789192","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-11-20","<p>Information on the number of pensioners who have had a reduction to the size of pension pay-outs is not collated centrally and could only be provided at a disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>This private arrangement is a feature of what are sometimes called integrated pension schemes. These schemes were designed to avoid additional contributions from sponsors and members by taking account of some or all of the State Pension when calculating the amount of occupational pension payable. The arrangement is set out in scheme rules which would have been available to members when they joined the scheme.</p><p> </p><p>Such arrangements are not a Department for Work and Pensions matter. There are no plans to legislate to compel schemes to withdraw an integration arrangement. Any retrospective change would impose significant additional unplanned costs. Pension scheme rules on the calculation of benefits are many and varied, and must remain a matter for employers and scheme trustees to decide.</p><p> </p><p>The Department has not issued any guidance on the effect of integrated pension schemes. However, there is an information note for Trustees, which is available on The Pensions Regulator website:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.thepensionsregulator.gov.uk/docs/changes-state-pension-age-dwp-june-2016.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.thepensionsregulator.gov.uk/docs/changes-state-pension-age-dwp-june-2016.pdf</a></p><p> </p>","Hexham","Guy Opperman","112571 ; 112660","2017-11-20T14:58:55.273Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789192/answer","Biography information for Guy Opperman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789192/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789192/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-11-14","Pensions: Repayments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what guidance his Department has issued on the effect of pension clauses.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","112905"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789193","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-11-20","<p>All Healthcare Professionals conducting Work Capability Assessments receive extensive training regarding autism spectrum disorders as part of their initial new entrant training. This training programme includes simulated assessments covering claimants with autism and learning disabilities to allow Healthcare Professionals to develop appropriate consultation skills. All Healthcare Professionals have access to condition specific information on autism which is quality assured by external reviewers. Healthcare Professionals are further supported by Functional Champions who are available to provide advice to Healthcare Professionals on particular conditions including autism before, during or after an assessment.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-11-20T15:48:03.723Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789193/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789193/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789193/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-11-14","Work Capability Assessment: Autism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether people administering work capability assessments are required to undertake training on autism and autistic spectrum disorders; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","112878"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789194","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-11-20","<p>I can confirm contingency planning is a requirement for any major procurement and DWP is monitoring the situation. I can also advise that direct engagement between Interserve and the incumbent provider is under way regarding TUPE transfer to ensure the successful implementation and handover of service delivery.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-11-20T16:19:58.63Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789194/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789194/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789194/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-11-14","Department for Work and Pensions: Interserve","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what contingency plans his Department has put in place to protect his Department's staff who are subject to TUPE transfer, in the event that Interserve the contractor for cleaning, messengerial and other support functions, is unable to fulfil its contract; and if he will make a statement.","true","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","112868"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789195","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-11-20","<p>I can confirm all companies bidding for departmental work under CCS frameworks are subject to a full and rigorous review of their financial capability. A financial assessment of Interserve was completed prior to awarding the DWP FM Contract.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-11-20T16:46:49.587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789195/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789195/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789195/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-11-14","Department for Work and Pensions: Interserve","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment his Department made of the financial sustainability of the company, Interserve, prior to awarding that company the contract for cleaning, messengerial and other support functions for his Department; and if he will make a statement.","true","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","112867"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789196","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-11-20","<p>I can confirm an evaluation of Interserve’s capability and capacity to deliver DWP’s FM requirements was completed before the award of contract - and can further confirm the mobilisation of the Facilities Management contract is proceeding to plan.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-11-20T16:40:31.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789196/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789196/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789196/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-11-14","Department for Work and Pensions: Interserve","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment his Department made of the suitability of Interserve as a fit and proper company before the award of the contract for cleaning, messengerial and other support functions; and if he will make a statement.","true","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","112853"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789197","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-11-22","<p>The Department for Work and Pensions supports work coaches to build a strong relationship with all claimants through a comprehensive training and accreditation programme. This includes training to understand specific claimant needs. DWP has undertaken an extensive autism and neurodiversity training programme to upskill staff across the Jobcentre Plus network, reaching 1200 staff members. This was delivered by Autism Alliance UK and was facilitated by disabled people with autistic spectrum conditions.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-11-22T11:31:48.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789197/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789197/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789197/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-11-14","Jobcentre Plus: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if his Department will develop scientific training in autism for work coaches in Jobcentre Plus.","false","Biography information for Stephanie Peacock","Barnsley East","Stephanie Peacock","112818"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789198","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-11-21","<p>In October 2016 we published Improving Lives: the Work, Health and Disability Green Paper, setting out the Government’s approach to work and health and inviting views on a ten-year strategy for reform.</p><p> </p><p>We engaged with a wide range of stakeholders and others with an interest during the Green Paper consultation period and received around 6,000 responses. We are working towards a publication later this year, which will provide an update on the work we have been doing since the Green Paper, respond to the consultation, and set out our next steps.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","113457","2017-11-21T13:32:49.92Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789198/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789198/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789198/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-11-14","Work Capability Assessment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 6 November 2017 to Question 110670, on work capability assessment, when he plans to publish the document setting out his Department's recent work, its response to the consultation and its next steps.","false","Biography information for Dr Lisa Cameron","East Kilbride, Strathaven and Lesmahagow","Dr Lisa Cameron","112820"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789199","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-11-21","<p>Our approach has primarily been to work with Remploy and other partners and charities, using their effective networks and channels to reach potential recipients and raise awareness. We have also worked extensively to promote the Access to Work Scheme via Disability Confident with stakeholders and partners such as the impairment specific charities and health practitioners.</p><p> </p><p>In addition we have made marketing funding available to produce materials and secure presences at appropriate conferences and events.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-11-21T15:05:58.69Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789199/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789199/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789199/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-11-14","Access to Work Programme: Publicity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps his Department is taking to raise awareness of, and promote, the Access to Work programme.","false","Biography information for Dr Lisa Cameron","East Kilbride, Strathaven and Lesmahagow","Dr Lisa Cameron","112822"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789200","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-11-20","<p>The Government takes the safety of fireworks very seriously. Regulations are currently in place which control the sale of fireworks to both consumers and professional display operators. Experience has shown that the current regulations strike the right balance between the enjoyment of fireworks by the public and restricting the sale and use of fireworks for public safety reasons.</p><p> </p><p>Certain dangerous items are already banned for sale in the UK. These include bangers and jumping jacks, among others. Such items are prohibited regardless of whether they are approved for sale in other EU countries. This removes from sale higher risk fireworks which could lead to injury.</p><p> </p><p>We will continue to focus on reducing accidents and nuisance by encouraging industry, retailers and others to promote the responsible sale and use of fireworks through guidance and public education.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-11-20T15:28:04.93Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789200/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789200/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789200/answer",,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-11-14","Fireworks: Sales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment his Department has made of the effectiveness of existing legislation regulating the sale of fireworks.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","112830"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789201","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-11-20","<p>The Government is considering all options for the UK’s future participation, or otherwise, in the EU Emissions Trading System after our exit from the EU. The effect on the cost of EU allowances will depend on the nature of the UK’s future relationship with the System and will be taken into account as part of this consideration.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2017-11-20T14:52:33.64Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789201/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789201/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789201/answer",,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-11-14","EU Emissions Trading Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether the Government has made an assessment of the effect of the UK's withdrawal from the EU on the cost of EU allowances.","false","Biography information for Stephen Kinnock","Aberavon","Stephen Kinnock","112848"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789202","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-11-21","<p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The Government recognises the potential long-term value of small modular reactor (SMR) technology and in October announced £7m funding over the next 2 years to build capacity of the UK nuclear regulators to support and assess advanced nuclear technologies like SMRs. We expect to make further announcements of SMR policy in the coming months.</p><p> </p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-11-21T10:41:34.693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789202/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789202/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789202/answer",,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-11-14","Nuclear Power","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what steps his Department is taking to introduce small modular reactors to the UK.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","112907"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789203","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-11-21","<p>No decisions have yet been made on our future relationship with the EU's agencies and bodies after leaving the EU. We are seeking a deep and special partnership with the European Union. Our relationship with the European Union's agencies and bodies, including the European Agency for Safety and Health at Work, will be evaluated on this basis upon exit</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-11-21T13:34:58.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789203/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789203/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789203/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-11-14","European Agency for Safety and Health At Work","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether the UK plans to seek observer status at the European Agency for Safety and Health at Work after the UK has left the EU.","false","Biography information for Stephen Kinnock","Aberavon","Stephen Kinnock","112900"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789204","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-11-20","<p>No decisions have yet been made on our future relationship with the EU's agencies and bodies after leaving the EU. We are seeking a deep and special partnership with the European Union. Our relationship with the European Union's agencies and bodies, including the European Foundation for the Improvement of Living and Working Conditions, upon exit will be evaluated on this basis.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-11-20T15:14:31.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789204/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789204/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789204/answer",,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-11-14","European Foundation for the Improvement of Living and Working Conditions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether the UK plans to seek formal co-operation with the European Foundation for the Improvement of Living and Working Conditions after the UK has left the EU.","false","Biography information for Stephen Kinnock","Aberavon","Stephen Kinnock","112901"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789205","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-11-20","<p>The Government published the joint BEIS/Ofgem <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/upgrading-our-energy-system-smart-systems-and-flexibility-plan" target="_blank">Smart Systems and Flexibility Plan</a> in 2017. The Plan outlines a series of actions to support the transition to a smart energy system which could save the UK an estimated £17 to £40 billion up to 2050. Some actions can benefit all consumers, including energy intensive industries. Particular measures in the Plan that could benefit these industries are improving access to the capacity market and changing the licensing regime around battery storage. Additionally, Government continues to fully support National Grid’s <a href="http://powerresponsive.com/" target="_blank">Power Responsive initiative</a> to increase the opportunities for industrial consumers to participate in demand side response.</p><p>BEIS Ministers and officials have regular discussions with representative of energy intensive industries on a range of energy-related issues, including smart grids.</p><p> </p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-11-20T14:30:12.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789205/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789205/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789205/answer",,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-11-14","Energy Intensive Industries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment his Department has made of the potential effect of moving to a Smart Grid on energy-intensive industries; and what discussions he has had with representatives of such industries.","false","Biography information for Mike Amesbury","Weaver Vale","Mike Amesbury","113018"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789206","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-11-20","<p>The Government welcomes the work and recommendations of the Law Commission which it has carried out in regards to consumer prepayments on retailer insolvency.</p><p>The Government has been in discussions with the Law Commission on this important issue and is considering its response.</p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-11-20T15:13:23.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789206/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789206/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789206/answer",,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-11-14","Retail Trade: Insolvency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, when he plans to respond to the report of the Law Commission, Consumer Prepayments on Retailer Insolvency, HC 543, published on 13 July 2016.","false","Biography information for Jessica Morden","Newport East","Jessica Morden","112978"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789207","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-11-20","<p>As set out in the Clean Growth Strategy, the Government intends to consult shortly on options to strengthen the domestic private rented sector minimum energy efficiency standard regulations.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2017-11-20T14:30:59.55Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789207/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789207/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789207/answer",,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-11-14","Energy: Private Rented Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, with reference to paragraph two of page 77 of the Clean Growth Strategy, when the consultation on making the private rented sector energy efficiency regulations more effective will open.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","112892"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789208","Department for International Trade","false","2017-11-20","<p>A list of countries with which the European Union has trade agreements in place is available on the European Commission website: <a href="http://ec.europa.eu/trade/policy/countries-and-regions/negotiations-and-agreements/#_in-place" target="_blank">http://ec.europa.eu/trade/policy/countries-and-regions/negotiations-and-agreements/#_in-place</a></p><p>Through a combination of ministerial and official engagements, the Department for International Trade is currently engaging with all countries with which the EU has trade agreements to discuss continuity of current trading arrangements as the UK leaves the EU.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-11-20T10:57:50.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789208/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789208/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789208/answer",,,,,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-11-14","EU External Trade","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, with which countries the EU has trade deals; and how many of those countries he has visited since taking office.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","112931"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789209","Department for International Trade","false","2017-11-20","<p>As the Government has set out in both the Department for International Trade’s (DIT) White Paper – ‘Preparing for our future UK trade policy’ – and the recently published Trade Bill , DIT is engaging with all countries with which the European Union currently has free trade agreements, with a view to replicating as far as possible the effects of existing agreements as the United Kingdom leaves the European Union.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-11-20T11:23:19.163Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789209/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789209/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789209/answer",,,,,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-11-14","EU External Trade","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what discussions he has had with countries that the EU has trade deals with about the operation of free trade agreements after March 2019.","false","Biography information for Kirsty Blackman","Aberdeen North","Kirsty Blackman","112804"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789210","Department for International Trade","false","2017-11-20","<p>As the Government has set out in both the Department for International Trade’s (DIT) White Paper – ‘Preparing for our future UK trade policy’ – and the recently published Trade Bill. DIT is engaging with all countries with which the European Union currently has free trade agreements, with a view to replicating as far as possible the effects of existing agreements as the United Kingdom leaves the European Union.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","112804","2017-11-20T11:23:19.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789210/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789210/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789210/answer",,,,,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-11-14","EU External Trade","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what plans he has to maintain elements of existing free trade agreements between the EU and other countries when the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Kirsty Blackman","Aberdeen North","Kirsty Blackman","112805"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789211","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2017-11-21","<p>We have been consistently clear that we want an early agreement on the rights of all EU citizens in the UK and UK nationals in the EU, on a reciprocal basis - of course, this includes non-UK EU nationals currently working in the Civil Service in the UK, to whom fall under this agreement.</p><p> </p><p>We recognise the valuable contribution of all civil servants, including the contribution that those who come from EU countries make. We welcome those with the skills and expertise to make our nation better still.</p><p> </p><p>We are continuing negotiations in a constructive way and are determined to reach agreement.</p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-11-21T18:08:26.44Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789211/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789211/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789211/answer",,,,,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2017-11-14","Civil Servants: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what discussions his Department has had with Michel Barnier on the future of non-UK EU citizens working in the Civil Service in the UK after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","112828"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789212","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-11-21","<p>The UK has world leading standards of food safety and quality, backed by a rigorous legislative framework. The EU (Withdrawal) Bill will ensure we are able to maintain these high standards once the UK leaves the European Union.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is committed to ensuring high food standards at home, and promoting high standards internationally. We will ensure there is a food standards framework in place that protects consumer interests, maximises confidence, and facilitates international trade.</p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-11-21T13:59:01.31Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789212/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789212/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789212/answer",,,,,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-11-14","Food: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what steps he is taking to ensure that food standards will be maintained after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Laura Pidcock","North West Durham","Laura Pidcock","113007"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789213","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-11-22","<p>As part of our work preparing to make a success of our departure from the European Union, we are carrying out a broad range of sectoral analysis, in including agriculture, as you would expect a responsible Government to do.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>Leaving the EU presents a major opportunity for UK agriculture. The Agriculture Bill will provide stability to farmers as we leave the EU. It will support our farmers to compete domestically and on the global market, allowing us to grow, sell and export more great British food. The bill includes measures to ensure that after we leave the EU, and therefore the Common Agricultural Policy, we have an effective system in place to support UK farmers and protect our natural environment.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is committed to getting the best possible deal for the United Kingdom - a deal that works for all parts of the UK, including the North East. We will continue to engage with businesses and industry bodies from all sectors of the economy, and all regions of the UK, in order to inform our negotiations with the EU.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-11-22T17:01:21.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789213/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789213/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789213/answer",,,,,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-11-14","Exports: North West Durham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what assessment the Government has made of the effect of the UK leaving the EU on exports from farms in North West Durham constituency.","false","Biography information for Laura Pidcock","North West Durham","Laura Pidcock","113004"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789214","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-11-23","<p>The Government has been clear that safeguarding the rights of UK and EU citizens, including EEA and Swiss nationals, is our first priority in negotiations. The UK’s published policy paper, ‘Safeguarding the position of EU citizens in the UK and UK nationals in the EU’, set out our offer on citizens’ rights to the EU and stated that we would discuss similar arrangements with Switzerland and the non-EU EEA states of Norway, Iceland and Liechtenstein (collectively referred to as ‘the EFTA states’ in the publication). We have already commenced constructive official-level scoping talks with all four states on citizens' rights.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-11-23T16:54:51.043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789214/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789214/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789214/answer",,,,,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-11-14","British Nationals Abroad: Switzerland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what his policy is on protecting the existing rights of British citizens residing in Switzerland after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Sir Vince Cable","Twickenham","Sir Vince Cable","112941"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789215","Home Office","false","2017-11-17","<p>We are considering a range of options for our future immigration arrangements and are clear that we must manage the process properly so that the system serves the national interest.</p><p> </p><p>On 27 July 2017, we commissioned the independent Migration Advisory Committee (MAC) to advise on the economic and social impacts of the UK’s exit from the European Union and also on how the UK’s immigration system should be aligned with a modern industrial strategy. As part of this, the MAC has been asked to consider a number of factors including skill level.</p><p>They are due to report on their findings in September 2018.</p><p> </p><p>Full details about the MAC commission can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/migration-advisory-committee" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/migration-advisory-committee</a></p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","112964 ; 112965","2017-11-17T09:21:54.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789215/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789215/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789215/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-11-14","Skilled Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment her Department has made of the value to the UK economy of mid-level skills or those at Standard Occupational Classification levels 2 and 3; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Siobhain McDonagh","Mitcham and Morden","Siobhain McDonagh","112963"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789216","Home Office","false","2017-11-17","<p>We are considering a range of options for our future immigration arrangements and are clear that we must manage the process properly so that the system serves the national interest.</p><p> </p><p>On 27 July 2017, we commissioned the independent Migration Advisory Committee (MAC) to advise on the economic and social impacts of the UK’s exit from the European Union and also on how the UK’s immigration system should be aligned with a modern industrial strategy. As part of this, the MAC has been asked to consider a number of factors including skill level.</p><p>They are due to report on their findings in September 2018.</p><p> </p><p>Full details about the MAC commission can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/migration-advisory-committee" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/migration-advisory-committee</a></p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","112963 ; 112965","2017-11-17T09:21:55.013Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789216/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789216/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789216/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-11-14","Skilled Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what external engagement her Department is engaged in to improve its understanding of the importance to the UK economy of access to mid-skilled labour or labour rated at Standard Occupational Classification skill levels 2 and 3; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Siobhain McDonagh","Mitcham and Morden","Siobhain McDonagh","112964"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789217","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-11-23","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given to the hon. Member for Kingston upon Hull North on 7 September 2017, UIN 7210.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>We do not hold information centrally about OGD’s use of lawyers.</p><p> </p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2017-11-23T14:34:00.88Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789217/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789217/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789217/answer",,,,,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-11-14","Legal Profession","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what the estimated cost to the public purse is of the additional lawyers who are being recruited to deal with the complexities of the work on the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","112960"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789219","Cabinet Office","false","2017-11-28","<p>Data concerning the number people registered to vote is held by Electoral Registration Officers, not by the Government. Each year, figures relating to the 1 December published register are provided by Electoral Registration Officers to the Office for National Statistics. After processing, the ONS then publishes the collected statistics on its website. You can find these at goo.gl/uXB4aK. Statistics relating to the 1 December 2017 register will be available in 2018.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-11-28T16:34:54.42Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789219/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789219/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789219/answer","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789219/answer/previousversion/23684","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789219/answer/previousversion/23684",,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-11-14","Electoral Register: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many more people were registered to vote as of 1 November 2017 than was the case at the time of the publication of the official 2015 electoral register in (a) Liverpool, Walton constituency, (b) Liverpool and (c) the North West.","false","Biography information for Dan Carden","Liverpool, Walton","Dan Carden","113051"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789220","Cabinet Office","false","2017-11-29","<p>There are no plans to replicate the Ministry of Justice Datalab model. A number of government departments have created and operate similar facilities where data can be securely accessed.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-11-29T11:14:01.043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789220/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789220/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789220/answer","Ashford","Damian Green","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789220/answer/previousversion/23685","Biography information for Damian Green","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789220/answer/previousversion/23685",,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-11-14","Government Departments: Databases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what plans he has to replicate the Ministry of Justice Data Lab model across other government departments.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","113063"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789221","HM Treasury","false","2017-11-20","<p>The creative sector tax reliefs provide support to ensure that creative industries thrive in the UK. There are currently seven schemes, covering film, animation, high-end TV, children’s TV, video games, theatre and orchestra.</p><p> </p><p>The government has recently legislated for an eighth creative sector relief, for museums and galleries.</p><p> </p><p>The government keeps all tax reliefs under review.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-11-20T14:42:55.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789221/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789221/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789221/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-11-14","Arts: Tax Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what plans he has to extend creative tax relief to new sectors.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","113062"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789222","HM Treasury","false","2017-11-20","<p>Total receipts from Betting and Gaming duties are published here:</p><p><a href="https://www.uktradeinfo.com/Statistics/Pages/TaxAndDutybulletins.aspx" target="_blank">https://www.uktradeinfo.com/Statistics/Pages/TaxAndDutybulletins.aspx</a></p><p> </p><p>A breakdown of revenue for General Betting Duty, Machine Games Duty and Remote Gaming Duty is included in this publication.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-11-20T11:15:12.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789222/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789222/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789222/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-11-14","Gambling: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what income the Exchequer has received from duty on (a) online gambling and (b) betting shop income in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","113121"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789223","HM Treasury","false","2017-11-20","<p>The remit of this initiative is for HMRC to identify those cases where enhanced employer education and support will improve the timeliness and quality of RTI submissions.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-11-20T14:46:10.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789223/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789223/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789223/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-11-14","Department for Work and Pensions: Revenue and Customs","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the remit and activities are of the joint initiatives between HM Revenue and Customs and the Department for Work and Pensions referred to as Late, Missing and Incorrect.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","113074"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789224","HM Treasury","false","2017-11-20","<p>The government has been working on the draft implementing legislation for Articles 15 and 16 of the EU Tobacco Products Directive with the Commission and other Member States. We are aware of concerns raised by businesses affected and have been working to try to ensure that the system adopted is effective, efficient and proportionate in tackling the trade in illicit tobacco products which puts public health at risk and avoids the payment of duty. A number of amendments have been made to the proposed regulations in line with meeting these objectives.</p><p> </p><p>We will continue to assess the impact and merits of the legislation and to work with businesses affected towards a successful implementation, given the timescales already set out in the Directive itself.</p><p> </p><p>The track and trace system to be introduced is separate from the existing retailer registration scheme in Northern Ireland. It will provide identification codes for retailers to be used when purchasing legitimate tobacco products. These codes can be obtained by suppliers on their behalf of retailers, if desired. The Directive also provides for the costs of the scheme, including the equipment needed to scan products through the supply chain, to be met by the tobacco industry.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","113136 ; 113137 ; 113138","2017-11-20T11:45:28.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789224/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789224/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789224/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-11-14","Tobacco: EU Action","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether the Government plans to delay UK implementation of the EU Commission's proposals for a European track and trace scheme for the tobacco market.","false","Biography information for Ian Paisley","North Ant